\N<Zuuteruka>Hey, just as promised, you showed up. Quite the sight to
behold, aren't you?
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Staring with such a scary face at our long-awaited
reunion. We were comrades once, weren't we?

\N<Segi>Don't joke around!! I won't let you forget what you did to
those comrades!

\N<Segi>To my father and mother...! I won't let you forget what you
did...!!

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... You're quite tenacious. Well, don't worry. I
haven't forgotten, and I'm certainly not looking for
forgiveness.
\N<Segi>What did you say...!?

\N<Zuuteruka>I'm saying I haven't forgotten anything. The feeling of
beating up your father... your master, and the sensation of
playing with your mother's big tits, I haven't forgotten any
of it.
\N<Segi>If you continue to insult my father and mother...!!

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, I'm not insulting anyone. I'm merely stating the
facts.

\N<Zuuteruka>I remember everything that happened after you guys
successfully escaped from "Dawn's Ear."
\N<Zuuteruka>Of course... that includes you too, right?
\N<Segi>Stop it...!!

\N<Zuuteruka>Calm down a bit. Did you come here just to curse at me?
That's not it, right? You came to talk about Yuia, didn't
you?

\N<Zuuteruka>So what are you going to do? There's a certain way to
behave, right? Otherwise, we can't have a conversation, can
we?
\N<Segi>Don't act like you understand...!

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Now then, have you calmed down? Now that our
emotional reunion is over, shall we continue last night's
conversation?
\N<Segi>Gah...!
\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe...
op_セギ04aa
\N<Segi>What are you...!?
op_セギ04a

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... What's wrong? You came to talk to me, right? You
just stopped by for that reason, didn't you? Eh?
\N<Segi>Gah...!?
\N<Segi>I have nothing to talk about with you...! Give Yuia back...!

\N<Zuuteruka>Give him back? If it's a request, there's a certain way to
ask, right? I just told you that. Do you even understand
your position?

\N<Segi>This isn't a request! It's a demand to you who took him away
unjustly...!

\N<Zuuteruka>What's unjust about it? The score has been settled. The
commander of the Luda garrison in this city... in other
words, me, was targeted for assassination. Where's the
injustice in that?

\N<Segi>That's why I'm saying it's nonsense...! Yuia would never do
such a thing...!

\N<Zuuteruka>I'm telling you the score has been settled. The crime
committed is significant. In other words, Yuia's arrest is
justified.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, let me say it one more time? The crime Yuia
committed is significant. Normally, that would mean
execution is inevitable.
\N<Segi>Don't joke around...!

\N<Segi>First of all, Yuia is currently participating in the
training soldiers' assembly. And he's advancing through the
ranks... During this time, his status and safety should be
guaranteed by your terms, shouldn't they!?

\N<Zuuteruka>Well, that's true but what's the reality? Is he in a
situation where he can participate in the training soldiers'
assembly now? The guarantee of status and safety is
conditional on participation in the assembly.

\N<Zuuteruka>On that note, what about Yuia? Can he continue to
participate properly from now on??
\N<Segi>That's why I'm saying...!
op_セギ04b
\N<Segi>Nngh...!?

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... What do you think? If there's a way for him to
participate in the training soldiers' assembly from inside a
cage, let me know, okay?
\N<Segi>Ugh...!
\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe...
Calm down. I need to calm down.

That's right... Disgust, resistance, anger. None of these
things are useful right now.

I didn't come here to be swayed by such temporary
emotions...
\N<Segi>Mmm... Mmm...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... The guarantee of one's safety is only for warriors
who are worth it. Do you think a criminal scum who attempted
assassination has that worth?
\N<Segi>Yuia-sama is... Mmm... not a criminal.

\N<Zuuteruka>Is that so? Then I'd like him to break out of his cell right
now and participate in the training soldiers' assembly.

\N<Zuuteruka>If he does, there would be no need for you to suffer like
this for your husband's sake. How about it? Can he do that
now?
\N<Segi>That is...

\N<Zuuteruka>Well, it's impossible, right? He's in a cage after all. So
there's no need to wait for the end of the training
soldiers' assembly to execute him, right?
\N<Segi>...
\N<Zuuteruka>...Do you understand? That there's no other way for Yuia?
\N<Segi>There is still... a way.
\N<Zuuteruka>Oh?

What I must do now... That is. What only I can do now...
That is.
\N<Segi>I will... I will go.

\N<Segi>If I participate in the training soldiers' assembly in place
of Yuia-sama... that should be fine, right...!?
\N<Zuuteruka>Oh...? You will?

\N<Segi>...Yes. And if I win until the end, that should be good
enough, right?

\N<Segi>If I continue to win in place of Yuia-sama, his status and
safety will be guaranteed during that time, right!?

\N<Zuuteruka>Hey hey, are you serious? I don't know if it's for the sake
of your beloved husband, but do you think you can make a
difference by participating?

\N<Zuuteruka>If so, that's naive. Very naive. The purpose of the training
soldiers' assembly is, as the name suggests, to select
strong soldiers and then recruit them as soldiers of Luda.

\N<Segi>I know that... I don't need to be told. I'm saying this
despite that.

\N<Zuuteruka>...Of course, the further you go, the higher you climb, the
weaker opponents disappear. Do you think you can beat them
all and win until the end?

\N<Segi>...I'm prepared. In place of Yuia-sama, I will protect Riia.
And Yuia-sama's life as well...
\N<Zuuteruka>...
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... I see, even if you don't volunteer, sooner or
later someone will have to stand in for Yuia.

\N<Zuuteruka>Then the remaining candidates are either his son or you.
Surely you wouldn't send your cute son into such a
battlefield.

\N<Segi>Exactly... I can't send Riia into such a battlefield. Then
there's only one thing I must do as a mother right now.

\N<Segi>Besides... even if Yuia-sama is not qualified as a warrior
now, there should be no problem with substituting another
warrior. What do you say, do you acknowledge it? Or not?
\N<Zuuteruka>...
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>You... are you really sane? Even if you are sane, do you
have any strategy to win without any proper combat
experience as a woman?

\N<Segi>It's not about having a strategy or confidence. There are
times when something must be done... that's all there is to
it.

\N<Segi>For the sake of someone important, even if I have to get
covered in mud and crawl on my knees, it's my duty to do
it... This is what it means.

\N<Segi>You wouldn't understand, walking a path of wielding
unreasonable violence and looking down on others... just for
that.
\N<Zuuteruka>...
\N<Segi>It's not because there's no other way, that's not my reason.
\N<Segi>For my precious person... I choose my own path.
op_セギ13a
\N<Zuuteruka>...

\N<Segi>I'll ask one more time... there should be no problem with
changing warriors. Do you acknowledge my participation or
not?

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, well... I understand how you feel. I see the
determination you've mustered with all the courage you have.

\N<Zuuteruka>It's not interesting to watch someone who steps into the
arena without any resolve or determination. Besides, such a
person could never grow into a decent soldier.

\N<Zuuteruka>In that sense... I'd really like to acknowledge your
participation, but...?

\N<Segi>If you're so understanding of my feelings, then skip the
roundabout talk and just acknowledge it already.
op_セギ05aa
\N<Segi>...
\N<Zuuteruka>...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Alright. Let's say we make it a fair exchange of
conditions.
\N<Segi>Exchange of conditions...?

\N<Zuuteruka>Yeah. As the commander of the Luda stationed in this town,
I can't just readily accept every request from the
residents. Hehehe... that's the tough part of serving the
court, right?
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Now, Segi. You understand why I came to this town,
don't you?

\N<Zuuteruka>The fact that you, me, and that guy Yuia met here again is
no coincidence. You realize that, right?
op_セギ05a

\N<Segi>Your reasons for coming to this town... To me, they're
nothing more than a coincidence. Naturally, I have no clue
about any other reasons.

\N<Zuuteruka>Oh, how cold... To treat a former comrade and childhood
friend like this.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>... You know what I desire, right? I'm not asking for a vast
fortune or your life.

\N<Zuuteruka>Literally... all you need to do is strip down for me. That
way we can both be satisfied with the negotiation. What do
you say? It's a cheap deal, isn't it...?
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... What do you say? You're making that face, but you
haven't completely forgotten about me, have you?

\N<Segi>You're still as filthy as ever... Don't ever joke about such
things again...

\N<Zuuteruka>We've been childhood friends since we were little. I learned
to fight from your parents and... I've been watching you
closely ever since.

\N<Segi>...And what of it? You're the one who destroyed that
relationship.

\N<Segi>...Didn't I tell you? I haven't forgotten what you and the
Luda soldiers surrounding you did to my father and mother.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... That was an unfortunate incident. But that's
separate from my personal feelings for you. I've said this
before, haven't I?

\N<Segi>Don't joke around... Those words have long since ceased to
linger even in the back of my mind.

\N<Segi>And... whatever delusion you're under, I am now Lord Yuia's
wife.

\N<Segi>Whether he is unjustly imprisoned or not, that doesn't
change. There's no skin of mine to bare for someone like
you.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Is that so? Then our conversation is over.
Tomorrow morning, Yuia will be decapitated, and his son will
be selected as a warrior in his place.

\N<Zuuteruka>It's a straight path to the typical tragedy of a family. But
in exchange... tonight, you can safely return home.
\N<Segi>...What are you trying to say?

\N<Zuuteruka>You said earlier that you choose your own path, right?
Exactly, right now there are two paths before you. It's up
to you which one to choose.

\N<Zuuteruka>One is a thorny path where you honor Yuia's chastity in
exchange for sending him and his son to hell together.

\N<Zuuteruka>The other is a path through a field of flowers where you
grant my pitiful wish and save both Yuia and his son.

\N<Zuuteruka>So... you understand, right...? Which path to choose is a
no-brainer if you think about it a little...
\N<Segi>...
\N<Segi>...Fine. I'll do as you wish.

\N<Segi>But... don't get me wrong. Granting your wish isn't a path
through a field of flowers. It's precisely the path through
hell's thorns.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Then it's all the more beautiful. A woman who
fulfills another man's wish for the sake of her husband and
son...

\N<Zuuteruka>Now that it's decided, let's not dawdle, shall we? I can
hardly wait any longer...
\N<Segi>...

\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... That's right, that's exactly what I want. That's
the spirit...

\N<Segi>...Have you already forgotten what I said just three steps
ago? I'm sure I told you never to say such things again...

\N<Zuuteruka>Oh, that's right, my bad. It seems I got a little too
excited. Let me admire those huge tits that drive your man
wild.

\N<Segi>...Don't talk so vulgarly. Besides... I have no intention of
making you that happy.

\N<Segi>More importantly, answer me quickly. About my participation
in the military training assembly...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Understood. What you say does make sense. I'll
acknowledge your participation. And I'll also ensure the
safety of Yuia and his son.
\N<Zuuteruka>Until the moment your heart breaks...
\N<Segi>...
\N<Segi>...Mm...ah.

\N<Segi>Wh-what do you mean inherited from my mother... Don't talk

\N<Zuuteruka>Talk as if I know... Well, who knows? Maybe I really do

\N<Segi>Th-that's nonsense... Do-don't say such...ah.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Well, that's fine. But let me confirm something,

\N<Segi>...Yes.

\N<Zuuteruka>That's good to hear. Then this will be quick. Let me add one

\N<Zuuteruka>Even if you're standing in for Yuia, your lack of combat

\N<Zuuteruka>First, before the main event of the military training

\N<Zuuteruka>Good, now that it's settled... First things first, take

NE_薬1
\N<Segi>Th-this is...

\N<Zuuteruka>You've seen it before, right? Yes, it's the same antidote
you took before entering the ruins.

\N<Segi>If you know that... then why this now? This medicine should

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, what you took was a significantly diluted version of

\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>You'll need to take this once more. That's a condition for

\N<Segi>...Why? What does taking this medicine have to do with me

\N<Zuuteruka>This drug is called "Mind Luda." It's a rare secret

\N<Zuuteruka>As you know, its primary effect is to counteract the strong
poison of the ruins. In other words, it can also be said to

\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>No matter what kind of talent for battle you may have... or

\N<Zuuteruka>The gap between you and the formidable warriors you're about

\N<Segi>...So this medicine is a means to bridge that gap, even if
just a little... In other words, that's what you're trying

\N<Zuuteruka>Something about fighting in place of her bedridden husband,

\N<Segi>Miss Irime...

NE_装束
\N<Segi>...What is this...?

\N<Zuuteruka>It's a battle attire woven with special techniques and

\N<Zuuteruka>An outfit optimized for battle... Together with "Mind

\N<Zuuteruka>Especially this one is a treasure for women who wish to

\N<Segi>...
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, so what will you do? However, without accepting
these two things—the medication and the battle attire—your

\N<Zuuteruka>It's not a battle that can be won with the frail arms of a

\N<Segi>...

\N<Segi>...Understood. I'll do as you say, right...? But before

\N<Zuuteruka>Huh? The guy's a criminal now, you know? It's not so simple

\N<Segi>I don't intend to ask for a long conversation. Just... I

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Well, alright. I'll take you to him. You might as

\N<Zuuteruka>He must be worried about it too. And even if you don't tell
